      <section eId="sec_9_10_184">
        <num>9-10-184</num>
        <content>
          <p>In the trial of a civil action for personal injuries, counsel shall be allowed to argue the worth or monetary value of pain and suffering to the jury; provided, however, that any such argument shall conform to the evidence or reasonable deductions from the evidence in the case.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1960, p. 174, ยง 1.)</p>
